==Depiction ==
<div style="background-color:#00000000; margin:1em; padding:5px 80px; border:0px solid #00000000">
The trees stand tall, each leaf a piercing needle. They put the land into a dark canopy, leaving behind a cold, blue, dim planet. The ground is wet, your socks are wet. The ground is moss, often sprinkled with sinewy roots and large ferns. It is tenebrous, coming upon the rare clearing is a relief. It would be the one place where something could be seen, except for the sky. The sky that gifts.

The sky shines. Each dot a perfectly glowing star, all of them crocheted together into constellations. While such an "perfect" thing cannot exist, it truly is perfect. They lie higher than us, behind the sky. What could they think? What do they look like? We can never know.

But why must they exist above our lightless planet? What intrigue may it offer? The sky piercing trees? The hollow caves? Or does our core give them their energy? So many unanswered questions, only a prophet could answer. A prophet who gets their voice from the skies, a prophet who will give us the pretty truth. All we can do is hope that their coming will be tomorrow.

Oh, if your prophets came back alive! Oh, if your prophets weren't swallowed by the ground! Oh, if they could speak! Do you prefer to die? You hold knowledge we will never have. Is the knowledge that immoral, it's better to forget it? To fall down from your constellation-bound home, and strike the core?

Why must our sky cry? Cry white tears which set on the ground. The cold it brings cannot be borne, our crops die from it. Why must you punish? Why must it not be rain tears that come from your gorgeous eyes? What could've hurt you? Stars are incomprehensible large. We're just ants in your playground. There must be nothing our great mother can cry over. Yet you do and punish us for it.

For the tallest things that grow are our colossal trees which pierce the sky. Are they reaching out for you, great mother? Is that their devotion towards you? Its unfair. We are small. They are big. The contest was already won by them before it even began. We cannot see you due to that contest. We cannot see what's in front of us. We cannot know where is where, what is what. Our lights aren't enough — will never be enough.
</div>
{{Blurimage|file=Constellation.jpg|hovertext=shining|caption=So the stars gave us the gift of life,|width=500px|align=center}}

[[File:Ursa Major Rose.gif|center|link=]]

==The Gifts==
<div style="background-color:#00000000; margin:1em; padding:5px 80px; border:0px solid #00000000">
For the 4th day of emendation, our stars gave us life. Created from nothing but dull matter, shaped into form. Gave us arms, gave us legs, gave us the ability to think.

A catchless deal was made in their rankings, we will never be harmed. We must feel only joy, feel only happiness, for the sky to never weep upon itself. Our old lived with them.

They made a place for us to live. Far from their celestial home, our planet formed. Born from nothingness, created by the stars' magic, it formed. Winding grass fields, places for all our villages, crops and for our life.
</div>
==The Lies==
<div style="background-color:#00000000; margin:1em; padding:5px 80px; border:0px solid #00000000">
Oh, what have we done to let them grow? Why didn't our stars protect us? Why would our stars not protect us? We are the only creation of them that holds meaning. Yet you let them grow. Let them grow and destroy our harmony. Let them grow to hurt the sky and make it cry. Let them grow to not be breakable. Let them grow... simply to let them grow. Oh, mother great sky, you obscured our vision of you! They cover your beauty by a dark we cannot escape! Why won't you save us?

They kept growing. We did nothing wrong, yet we were still punished. Punished for the act of existing, punished for the act of breathing. "Don't breathe" is the same as not living. And what is living if we can't see your pretty face?

They hurt the sky and made it weep. Punctured it, made it cry. It takes time for it to heal; it will weep for many days. Many days of hardship for us. Your children freeze, your children die. Who will be there once we all lose our dying heat? Was it all a lie? Are there [[Entity List|more]] creations?
</div>
==The Truth==
<div style="background-color:#00000000; margin:1em; padding:5px 80px; border:0px solid #00000000">
We have to live in harshness. We cannot know if our day is the last, when the giants will best us, when the stars will abandon us. Or have they already? It wouldn't be a stretch considering the rigorous conditions that we have to endure. Are we no longer special? Did the trees steal our role? Why would they need to reach the stars? They were never made by them. They existed one day. And grower.

When will we be able to escape? Escape these giants? Would that be abandoning our stars? Abandoning the only ones who ''ever'' cared for us? When will we be able to reach the stars? Be next to them, tug their shirts, cry on their shoulders? Is it too much to ask for? Our first have lived with you. Why can't we?

Will the prophet clear these up? Why do we have to lose? Why can't we be like our elderly who died? The stars will accept us one day. They will abandon the insatiable trees and care for their children once more.

Are the trees truly insatiable? We are the ones desperate for the stars. We have an insatiable desire to reach the stars.

Why does suffering exist if the universe is beautiful?


Were my ramblings simply a delusion?</div>
